# React Native + FSD + Redux Toolkit Rules

## Core Principles

- Type-safe TypeScript, strict mode, no `any`
- Functional components + hooks only
- **FSD architecture** (see below)
- **Redux Toolkit + RTK Query** for state & data (NO Zustand)
- **redux-persist + MMKV** for session persistence
- Performance: memo, FlatList optimizations, avoid inline functions

## FSD Rules (mandatory)

src/
├── app/ # entry, store, navigation, providers, error-boundary
├── pages/ # full screens
├── features/ # user scenarios (favorites, toggle-favorite)
├── entities/ # business models (post)
├── widgets/ # reusable blocks (post-card, offline-banner)
└── shared/ # UI kit, theme, config, helpers, redux hooks

**Dependency direction:**  
`app → pages → widgets/features → entities → shared`  
(never import from higher layer into lower)

**Slice structure:**
slice/
├── ui/ # components only
├── model/ # Redux slice, selectors
├── api/ # RTK Query endpoints
├── lib/ # helpers
└── index.ts # public exports only

## Imports

- Use path alias `@/` for `src/`
- Cross-slice imports only through `index.ts`
- Typed Redux hooks: `@/shared/lib/redux`
- Env config: `@/shared/config/env`
- Theme tokens: `@/shared/theme`

## Redux Toolkit + RTK Query

- Store in `app/store.ts` – `configureStore`, add `api.reducerPath` & middleware
- Root reducer in `app/model/root-reducer.ts`
- Persist config in `app/persist-config.ts` with version + migrate
- Create API slices with `createApi`, auto-generate hooks
- Use generated hooks (useGetPostsQuery) in UI

## TypeScript & Naming

camelCase for vars/functions, PascalCase for components
Directory names: kebab-case

## Performance Essentials

React.memo for static props
useCallback/useMemo for heavy work
FlatList: removeClippedSubviews, maxToRenderPerBatch
No inline functions in renderItem or event handlers
No getItemLayout unless item height is truly fixed

## UI & Styling

StyleSheet.create() only
Use shared theme tokens (colors, spacing) — no hardcoded hex in components
Responsive: useWindowDimensions, flex
Images: react-native-fast-image

## Logging

No console.log in src/
Use `shared/lib/logger.ts` (dev-only output)

## What NOT to do

❌ Expo modules
❌ Zustand, MobX, plain Context for global state
❌ Cross-slice direct imports (use index.ts)
❌ Business logic inside UI components
❌ AsyncStorage for persist (use MMKV)

Always: UI-logic separation, RTK Query for API, follow FSD dependency rules.
